element.name: Bridge for Sale by Kili or bust, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit The Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: A simple cache in a County Kildare town which is fast becoming another suburb of sprawling Dublin. For the moment though it still retains a little of it's rural nature. The cache site is a very old remnant of that past but it is surrounded by all the trappings of modern progress as well. A very easy one!

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Mullingar Man
gps all over the place, but found it eventually, TFTC!

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Soupcooler
Gps playing up today so had to resort to using my instinct! Found after a bit of a search! TFTC!

2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by Spark_ie
GPS was playing games on me for ages, kept urging me to climb the metal fence and wander around the ruins.. I knew the cache couldn't be in there.. A call to the cache owner confirmed this suspicion, and a quick search nearby surrendered the cache to me. Having signed the log, I looked at the GPS and it was telling me 0m !!! It was 16m away 2 minutes ago ! Jeanie Mack! As for the cache name, makes total sense to me ... How couldn't it? [:)] TFTC, Spark_ie

2010-03-21T19:00:00Z : Found it by DoJoPa
TFTC, another quick find, but where is the bidge for sale?

2010-02-20T20:00:00Z : Didn't find it by culann
Search for anout 20mins in fading light but could not find it. GPS put me right on the spot but it failed me to find it. I will try again another day [:(]
